  Survey is given concerning the savings method for the vehicle routing problem. Results for several methods and data sets are compared. Furthermore, modifications of the savings method are presented which show less CPU time and reduced storage requirements. Therefore, the savings method can be implemented on microcomputers. Keywords Vehicle routing ; heuristics ; microcomputers Biles and Bradford, 1975 W.E. Biles, J.W. Bradford A heuristic approach to vehicle scheduling with due-date constraints ORSA National Meeting, Spring 1975, Chicago, IL (1975) Buxey, 1979 G.M. Buxey The vehicle scheduling problem and Monte Carlo simulation Journal of Operational Research Society, 30 (1979), pp. 563–573 Christofides and Eilon, 1969 N. Christofides, S. Eilon An algorithm for the vehicle dispatching problem Operational Research Quarterly, 20 (1969), pp. 309–318 Christofides et al., 1979 N. Christofides, A. Mingozzi, P. Toth The vehicle routing problem N. Christofides (Ed.), et al. , Combinatorial Optimization, Wiley, Chichester-New York-Brisbane-Toronto (1979), pp. 315–338 Clarke and Wright, 1964 G. Clarke, J.W. Wright Scheduling of vehicles from a central depot to a number of delivery points Operations Research, 12 (1964), pp. 568–581 Fisher and Jaikumar, 1981 M.L. Fisher, R. Jaikumar A generalized assignment heuristic for vehicle routing Networks, 11 (1981), pp. 109–124 Foster and Ryan, 1976 B.A. Foster, D.M. Ryan An integer programming approach to the vehicle scheduling problem Operational Research Quarterly, 27 (1976), pp. 367–384 Gaskell, 1967 T.J. Gaskell Bases for vehicle fleet scheduling Operational Research Quarterly, 18 (1967), pp. 281–295 Gillett and Miller, 1976 B.E. Gillett, L.R. Miller A heuristic algorithm for the vehicle-dispatch problem Operations Research (1976), pp. 340–349 Gillett and Johnson, 1974 B.E. Gillett, J. Johnson Sweep algorithm for the multiple depot vehicle dispatch problem ORSA National Meeting, Fall 1974, San Juan (1974) Golden et al., 1977 B.L.